cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.IT 

This paper deals with a security issue in distance-measurement techniques used in mobile autonomous systems, robots, and cyber-physical systems. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.RO (Robotics), and cs.IT (Information Theory). Among these categories, cs.CR is the most likely category as the paper deals with a security issue. The other categories are also relevant as the paper discusses the use of Ultra-Wideband Enlargement Detection (UWB-ED) in mobile autonomous systems, robots, and cyber-physical systems, which are related to networking, control, robotics, and information theory.
